HEADWORD: Disaffirmance
<hw>Dis`af*firm"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of disaffirming; denial; negation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Overthrow or annulment by the
decision of a superior tribunal; <as>as, <ex>disaffirmance</ex> of
judgment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disaffirmation</ent>⟦br⟧
